      <![CDATA[<p>I recently watched a thought-provoking conversation between Professor Di Dongsheng and Wang Xiao. Professor Di raised a fascinating thesis about the future of the AI investment boom.</p><div class="video-container"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_qyaGpzqn3Y" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><p>His argument goes like this:</p><ul><li>The <strong>AI bubble</strong> (if it is one) has been fuelled by massive, sustained capital inflows.</li><li>A significant portion of that “dry powder” comes from <strong>Middle Eastern PE funds</strong> – sovereign wealth vehicles that have benefited from decades of oil surpluses.</li><li>However, the ongoing geopolitical turmoil in the Middle East has severely disrupted their primary cash flow: <strong>petrodollar revenues</strong>.</li></ul><h2 id="The-Gold–Oil-Decoupling"><a href="#The-Gold–Oil-Decoupling" class="headerlink" title="The Gold–Oil Decoupling"></a>The Gold–Oil Decoupling</h2><p>Here’s where it gets interesting. Recently, we have observed a clear <strong>divergence</strong> between gold and crude oil prices:</p><ul><li>Middle East tensions rise → oil prices spike (supply fears).</li><li>Yet, instead of safe‑haven gold rallying alongside oil, <strong>gold prices have dropped</strong>.</li></ul><p>Professor Di interprets this as a liquidity squeeze: cash‑strapped Middle Eastern funds are <strong>selling their accumulated gold reserves</strong> to cover immediate fiscal needs. Gold becomes a source of liquidity, not a hedge, in times of their own distress.</p><h2 id="The-Inevitable-Corollary"><a href="#The-Inevitable-Corollary" class="headerlink" title="The Inevitable Corollary"></a>The Inevitable Corollary</h2><p>If this interpretation is correct, then we can derive a simple but powerful signal:</p><blockquote><p>When the normal relationship resumes – i.e., oil spikes <em>and</em> gold spikes together during Middle East escalations – it will mean that gold reserves have been largely depleted.</p></blockquote><p>At that point, these same PE funds may be forced to liquidate their most liquid risky assets to raise cash. And what is more liquid and over‑valued right now than <strong>AI startup stakes</strong>?</p><p>That could be the pin that pricks the AI bubble.</p><h2 id="A-Small-Monitoring-Tool"><a href="#A-Small-Monitoring-Tool" class="headerlink" title="A Small Monitoring Tool"></a>A Small Monitoring Tool</h2><p>I am neither an economist nor a geopolitical analyst – just a curious coder. So I built a lightweight tool that fetches recent gold (XAU) and crude oil (BRENT) prices from the <strong>Alpha Vantage API</strong> and plots them after simple normalisation. You can grab your own free API key from <a href="https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key" title="" target="_blank">Alpha Vantage</a> to run the tool.</p><p>The goal is not to predict, but to <strong>observe</strong> when the decoupling starts to heal.</p><h2 id="Important-Disclaimer"><a href="#Important-Disclaimer" class="headerlink" title="Important Disclaimer"></a>Important Disclaimer</h2><p><strong>This is not investment advice.</strong></p><ul><li>I have no formal training in finance, economics, or political science.</li><li>The data is raw, the normalisation is rudimentary, and the interpretation is speculative.</li><li>Use this tool for observational purpose only.</li><li><strong>Regarding Alpha Vantage</strong>: This blog post and the accompanying tool do not provide or embed any API key – you must obtain your own key directly from <a href="https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key" title="" target="_blank">Alpha Vantage</a> and strictly comply with their terms of service, rate limits, and usage policies. I do not assume any responsibility for your use of their API or the data retrieved.</li></ul><div id="goldOilChartApp" class="gold-oil-chart-app">    <h1 class="gold-oil-title">📊 Gold vs Crude Oil · Price Comparison <span>Normalized</span></h1>    <div class="gold-oil-setup-panel">        <div class="gold-oil-date-group">            <label>📅 Start Date</label>            <input type="date" id="goldOilStartDate" value="2026-03-01">        </div>        <div class="gold-oil-api-group">            <label>🔑 Alpha Vantage API Key</label>            <input type="text" id="goldOilApiKey" placeholder="Enter your free API Key (alphavantage.co)" autocomplete="off">        </div>        <button id="goldOilFetchBtn"><span>⬇️</span> Fetch Live Data</button>        <button id="goldOilDemoBtn" style="background:#334155;"><span>📋</span> Use Demo Data</button>    </div>    <div class="gold-oil-csv-row">        <div class="gold-oil-csv-group">            <label>📁 Gold CSV (date,price)</label>            <input type="file" id="goldOilGoldCsv" accept=".csv, text/csv">        </div>        <div class="gold-oil-csv-group">            <label>📁 Oil CSV (date,price)</label>            <input type="file" id="goldOilOilCsv" accept=".csv, text/csv">        </div>        <button id="goldOilCsvLoadBtn"><span>📤</span> Load CSV Data</button>        <div class="gold-oil-status" id="goldOilStatus"><span>⏳</span> Awaiting Data</div>    </div>    <div class="gold-oil-controls">        <div class="gold-oil-method-tabs" id="goldOilMethodTabs">            <button class="gold-oil-method-btn active" data-method="index100">📈 Index (100)</button>            <button class="gold-oil-method-btn" data-method="minmax">📐 Min-Max (0-1)</button>            <button class="gold-oil-method-btn" data-method="zscore">📏 Z-score</button>            <button class="gold-oil-method-btn" data-method="raw">💰 Raw Prices (Dual Axis)</button>        </div>        <div class="gold-oil-legend-note">            <span><span class="gold-oil-gold-dot"></span> Gold (XAU/USD)</span>            <span><span class="gold-oil-oil-dot"></span> Crude Oil (BRENT)</span>        </div>    </div>    <div class="gold-oil-chart-wrapper"><canvas id="goldOilPriceChart"></canvas></div>    <div id="goldOilError" class="gold-oil-error-message" style="display: none;"></div>    <div class="gold-oil-footer-note">⚡ Supports API, demo data, or CSV upload · Auto-detects date formats · Adjustable start date</div></div><style>    #goldOilChartApp {        font-family: inherit;        max-width: 1100px;        width: 100%;        margin: 2rem auto;        background: #ffffff;        border-radius: 24px;        box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06), 0 6px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);        padding: 28px 24px 24px;        display: flex;        flex-direction: column;        gap: 22px;        border: 1px solid #f0f2f5;        box-sizing: border-box;        color: #1e293b;    }    #goldOilChartApp *,    #goldOilChartApp *::before,    #goldOilChartApp *::after {        box-sizing: border-box;        margin: 0;        padding: 0;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-title {        font-size: 1.9rem;        font-weight: 600;        color: #1e293b;        display: flex;        align-items: center;        gap: 10px;        margin-bottom: 4px;        letter-spacing: -0.5px;        border-bottom: 2px solid #f1f5f9;        padding-bottom: 16px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-title span {        background: #fbbf24;        color: #0f172a;        font-size: 0.9rem;        font-weight: 600;        padding: 4px 12px;        border-radius: 30px;        margin-left: 8px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-setup-panel {        background: #f8fafc;        border-radius: 18px;        padding: 18px 20px;        display: flex;        flex-wrap: wrap;        align-items: flex-end;        gap: 16px;        border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-api-group,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-group,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-date-group {        display: flex;        flex-direction: column;        gap: 6px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-api-group {        flex: 2;        min-width: 180px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-group {        flex: 1;        min-width: 160px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-date-group {        min-width: 140px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-group label,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-api-group label,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-date-group label {        font-weight: 600;        font-size: 0.85rem;        color: #475569;        letter-spacing: 0.3px;        text-transform: uppercase;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-api-group input,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-group input[type="file"],    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-date-group input[type="date"] {        color-scheme: light;        padding: 12px 14px;        border-radius: 12px;        border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;        background: white;        font-size: 0.9rem;        outline: none;        font-family: inherit;        width: 100%;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-api-group input:focus,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-group input[type="file"]:focus,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-date-group input[type="date"]:focus {        border-color: #3b82f6;        box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.2);    }    #goldOilChartApp button {        background: #0f172a;        color: white;        border: none;        padding: 12px 24px;        border-radius: 14px;        font-weight: 600;        font-size: 0.95rem;        cursor: pointer;        transition: 0.2s;        display: inline-flex;        align-items: center;        gap: 8px;        letter-spacing: 0.3px;        box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);        white-space: nowrap;        font-family: inherit;    }    #goldOilChartApp button:hover {        background: #1e293b;        transform: translateY(-1px);        box-shadow: 0 8px 18px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.18);    }    #goldOilChartApp button:disabled {        opacity: 0.5;        pointer-events: none;        background: #64748b;        box-shadow: none;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-row {        display: flex;        flex-wrap: wrap;        align-items: flex-end;        gap: 16px;        background: #f1f5f9;        border-radius: 16px;        padding: 14px 18px;        margin-top: 4px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-controls {        display: flex;        align-items: center;        justify-content: space-between;        flex-wrap: wrap;        gap: 12px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-tabs {        display: flex;        flex-wrap: wrap;        gap: 10px;        background: #f1f5f9;        padding: 6px;        border-radius: 16px;        width: fit-content;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-btn {        background: transparent;        color: #334155;        border: none;        padding: 10px 20px;        border-radius: 12px;        font-weight: 600;        font-size: 0.9rem;        cursor: pointer;        transition: 0.2s;        background: transparent;        box-shadow: none;        font-family: inherit;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-btn.active {        background: white;        color: #0f172a;        box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-btn:hover:not(.active) {        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-chart-wrapper {        position: relative;        height: 420px;        width: 100%;        background: #ffffff;        border-radius: 18px;        padding: 10px 8px 0 8px;        border: 1px solid #e9eef2;    }    #goldOilChartApp canvas {        display: block;        max-width: 100%;        width: 100% !important;        height: 100% !important;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-status {        font-size: 0.9rem;        color: #475569;        background: #f1f5f9;        padding: 8px 16px;        border-radius: 20px;        display: inline-flex;        align-items: center;        gap: 6px;        white-space: nowrap;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-legend-note {        display: flex;        gap: 24px;        font-size: 0.85rem;        color: #475569;        flex-wrap: wrap;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-gold-dot,    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-oil-dot {        display: inline-block;        width: 12px;        height: 12px;        border-radius: 4px;        margin-right: 6px;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-gold-dot {        background: #eab308;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-oil-dot {        background: #1e3a5f;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-error-message {        background: #fee2e2;        color: #991b1b;        padding: 12px 16px;        border-radius: 12px;        font-size: 0.9rem;        display: none;    }    #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-footer-note {        font-size: 0.8rem;        color: #64748b;        text-align: center;        border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;        padding-top: 14px;        margin-top: 8px;    }    /* 响应式适配 */    @media (max-width: 768px) {        #goldOilChartApp {            padding: 18px 14px 18px;            margin: 1rem auto;            border-radius: 16px;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-title {            font-size: 1.4rem;            flex-wrap: wrap;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-title span {            font-size: 0.75rem;            padding: 2px 10px;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-setup-panel,        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-row {            padding: 14px;            gap: 12px;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-chart-wrapper {            height: 300px;            padding: 6px 4px 0 4px;        }        #goldOilChartApp button {            padding: 10px 16px;            font-size: 0.85rem;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-btn {            padding: 8px 14px;            font-size: 0.8rem;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-controls {            flex-direction: column;            align-items: stretch;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-tabs {            width: 100%;            justify-content: center;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-legend-note {            justify-content: center;            gap: 16px;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-status {            font-size: 0.8rem;            padding: 6px 12px;        }    }    @media (max-width: 480px) {        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-chart-wrapper {            height: 240px;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-title {            font-size: 1.15rem;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-setup-panel,        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-row {            flex-direction: column;            align-items: stretch;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-api-group,        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-csv-group,        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-date-group {            min-width: unset;            width: 100%;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-tabs {            flex-wrap: wrap;            justify-content: center;        }        #goldOilChartApp .gold-oil-method-btn {            padding: 6px 12px;            font-size: 0.75rem;        }    }</style><script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.1/dist/chart.umd.min.js"></script><script>    (function() {        // ---- DOM refs ----        const startDateInput = document.getElementById('goldOilStartDate');        const apiKeyInput = document.getElementById('goldOilApiKey');        const fetchBtn = document.getElementById('goldOilFetchBtn');        const demoBtn = document.getElementById('goldOilDemoBtn');        const csvLoadBtn = document.getElementById('goldOilCsvLoadBtn');        const goldCsvInput = document.getElementById('goldOilGoldCsv');        const oilCsvInput = document.getElementById('goldOilOilCsv');        const statusBadge = document.getElementById('goldOilStatus');        const errorDiv = document.getElementById('goldOilError');        const methodButtons = document.querySelectorAll('#goldOilMethodTabs .gold-oil-method-btn');        const ctx = document.getElementById('goldOilPriceChart').getContext('2d');        let chart = null;        let rawGoldData = [];        let rawOilData = [];        let currentMethod = 'index100';        function getStartDate() {            return startDateInput.value || '2026-03-01';        }        // ---- Date utilities ----        function normalizeDateString(dateStr) {            if (!dateStr) return null;            const s = dateStr.trim();            if (/^\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}$/.test(s)) {                const d = new Date(s + 'T00:00:00');                if (!isNaN(d.getTime())) return s;            }            if (s.includes('/')) {                const parts = s.split('/');                if (parts.length === 3) {                    let month = parseInt(parts[0], 10);                    let day = parseInt(parts[1], 10);                    let year = parseInt(parts[2], 10);                    if (!isNaN(month) && !isNaN(day) && !isNaN(year)) {                        if (year < 100) year += 2000;                        const d = new Date(year, month - 1, day);                        if (!isNaN(d.getTime()) && d.getFullYear() === year && d.getMonth() === month - 1 && d                            .getDate() === day) {                            return `${year}-${String(month).padStart(2, '0')}-${String(day).padStart(2, '0')}`;                        }                    }                }            }            if (s.includes('/')) {                const parts = s.split('/');                if (parts.length === 3) {                    let p1 = parseInt(parts[0], 10),                        p2 = parseInt(parts[1], 10),                        p3 = parseInt(parts[2], 10);                    if (!isNaN(p1) && !isNaN(p2) && !isNaN(p3)) {                        let year = p3 < 100 ? p3 + 2000 : p3;                        if (p1 > 12 && p2 <= 12) {                            const d = new Date(year, p2 - 1, p1);                            if (!isNaN(d.getTime()) && d.getFullYear() === year && d.getMonth() === p2 - 1 && d                                .getDate() === p1) {                                return `${year}-${String(p2).padStart(2, '0')}-${String(p1).padStart(2, '0')}`;                            }                        }                    }                }            }            const fallback = new Date(s);            if (!isNaN(fallback.getTime())) {                return fallback.toISOString().slice(0, 10);            }            return null;        }        function parseDateForFilter(str) {            return new Date(str + 'T00:00:00');        }        function formatDate(date) {            const d = new Date(date);            return `${d.getFullYear()}-${String(d.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0')}-${String(d.getDate()).padStart(2, '0')}`;        }        function filterAndSort(dataArray) {            if (!Array.isArray(dataArray)) return [];            const start = parseDateForFilter(getStartDate());            return dataArray                .filter(item => {                    const d = parseDateForFilter(item.date);                    return d >= start && !isNaN(d.getTime());                })                .sort((a, b) => parseDateForFilter(a.date) - parseDateForFilter(b.date));        }        // ---- CSV parsing ----        function parseCSV(text, label) {            const lines = text.split(/\r?\n/).filter(line => line.trim() !== '');            if (lines.length === 0) throw new Error(`${label} CSV file is empty`);            let headerIndex = 0;            const firstLine = lines[0].toLowerCase().replace(/\s/g, '');            if (firstLine.includes('date') && firstLine.includes('price')) {                headerIndex = 1;            }            const result = [];            for (let i = headerIndex; i < lines.length; i++) {                const cols = lines[i].split(',').map(s => s.trim());                if (cols.length < 2) continue;                const rawDate = cols[0];                const price = parseFloat(cols[1]);                if (!rawDate || isNaN(price)) continue;                const standardDate = normalizeDateString(rawDate);                if (!standardDate) continue;                result.push({ date: standardDate, value: price });            }            if (result.length === 0) throw new Error(`No valid data in ${label} CSV`);            return result;        }        // ---- Transformation methods ----        function computeIndex100(data) {            if (data.length === 0) return [];            const base = data[0].value;            return data.map(d => ({ date: d.date, value: base === 0 ? 100 : (d.value / base) * 100 }));        }        function computeMinMax(data) {            if (data.length === 0) return [];            const vals = data.map(d => d.value);            const min = Math.min(...vals),                max = Math.max(...vals);            return data.map(d => ({ date: d.date, value: max === min ? 0.5 : (d.value - min) / (max - min) }));        }        function computeZScore(data) {            if (data.length === 0) return [];            const vals = data.map(d => d.value);            const n = vals.length;            const mean = vals.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / n;            const std = Math.sqrt(vals.reduce((s, v) => s + (v - mean) ** 2, 0) / n);            return data.map(d => ({ date: d.date, value: std === 0 ? 0 : (d.value - mean) / std }));        }        function transformData(gold, oil, method) {            let g, o;            switch (method) {                case 'index100':                    g = computeIndex100(gold);                    o = computeIndex100(oil);                    break;                case 'minmax':                    g = computeMinMax(gold);                    o = computeMinMax(oil);                    break;                case 'zscore':                    g = computeZScore(gold);                    o = computeZScore(oil);                    break;                default:                    g = gold.map(d => ({ ...d }));                    o = oil.map(d => ({ ...d }));            }            return { gold: g, oil: o };        }        // ---- Render chart ----        function renderChart(goldData, oilData, method) {            const { gold: gProc, oil: oProc } = transformData(goldData, oilData, method);            const labels = gProc.map(d => d.date);            const datasets = [{                label: 'Gold (XAU/USD)',                data: gProc.map(d => d.value),                borderColor: '#eab308',                backgroundColor: 'rgba(234,179,8,0.08)',                borderWidth: 2.8,                pointRadius: 1.5,                pointHoverRadius: 6,                tension: 0.25,                yAxisID: method === 'raw' ? 'y' : 'y',            }, {                label: 'Crude Oil (BRENT)',                data: oProc.map(d => d.value),                borderColor: '#1e3a5f',                backgroundColor: 'rgba(30,58,95,0.05)',                borderWidth: 2.8,                pointRadius: 1.5,                pointHoverRadius: 6,                tension: 0.25,                yAxisID: method === 'raw' ? 'y1' : 'y',            }];            const scales = {};            if (method === 'raw') {                scales.y = {                    type: 'linear',                    position: 'left',                    title: { display: true, text: 'Gold (USD/oz)' },                    grid: { color: '#e2e8f0' }                };                scales.y1 = {                    type: 'linear',                    position: 'right',                    title: { display: true, text: 'Oil (USD/bbl)' },                    grid: { drawOnChartArea: false }                };            } else {                let label = method === 'index100' ? 'Index (100)' : (method === 'minmax' ? 'Min-Max (0-1)' : 'Z-score');                scales.y = {                    type: 'linear',                    position: 'left',                    title: { display: true, text: label },                    grid: { color: '#e2e8f0' }                };            }            if (chart) chart.destroy();            chart = new Chart(ctx, {                type: 'line',                data: { labels, datasets },                options: {                    responsive: true,                    maintainAspectRatio: false,                    interaction: { mode: 'index', intersect: false },                    plugins: {                        tooltip: {                            callbacks: {                                label: (ctx) =>                                    `${ctx.dataset.label}: ${method === 'raw' ? ctx.parsed.y.toFixed(2) : ctx.parsed.y.toFixed(4)}`                            }                        },                        legend: { labels: { usePointStyle: true, boxWidth: 8, padding: 16 } }                    },                    scales: {                        ...scales,                        x: { grid: { display: false }, ticks: { maxTicksLimit: 10 } }                    }                }            });        }        function setStatus(text, ok = true) {            statusBadge.innerHTML = `<span>${ok ? '✅' : '⚠️'}</span> ${text}`;        }        function showError(msg) {            errorDiv.style.display = 'block';            errorDiv.textContent = '❌ ' + msg;        }        function hideError() {            errorDiv.style.display = 'none';        }        // ---- Core alignment (Inner Join on dates) ----        function alignAndSetData(goldArr, oilArr, sourceLabel) {            const filteredGold = filterAndSort(goldArr);            const filteredOil = filterAndSort(oilArr);            if (filteredGold.length === 0 || filteredOil.length === 0) {                throw new Error(`${sourceLabel} data has no valid records from ${getStartDate()}.`);            }            const goldMap = new Map(filteredGold.map(d => [d.date, d.value]));            const oilMap = new Map(filteredOil.map(d => [d.date, d.value]));            const commonDates = [...goldMap.keys()].filter(date => oilMap.has(date)).sort((a, b) => new Date(a) - new Date(            b));            if (commonDates.length === 0) {                throw new Error(`No common trading days found between Gold and Oil from ${getStartDate()}.`);            }            const commonGold = commonDates.map(date => ({ date, value: goldMap.get(date) }));            const commonOil = commonDates.map(date => ({ date, value: oilMap.get(date) }));            rawGoldData = goldArr;            rawOilData = oilArr;            setStatus(                `${sourceLabel} · ${commonGold.length} trading days (${commonGold[0].date} ~ ${commonGold[commonGold.length - 1].date})`,                true);            renderChart(commonGold, commonOil, currentMethod);        }        function reapplyFilterAndRender() {            if (rawGoldData.length === 0 || rawOilData.length === 0) return;            try {                const filteredGold = filterAndSort(rawGoldData);                const filteredOil = filterAndSort(rawOilData);                const goldMap = new Map(filteredGold.map(d => [d.date, d.value]));                const oilMap = new Map(filteredOil.map(d => [d.date, d.value]));                const commonDates = [...goldMap.keys()].filter(date => oilMap.has(date)).sort((a, b) => new Date(a) - new Date(                    b));                if (commonDates.length === 0) {                    showError(`No common trading days found from ${getStartDate()}.`);                    setStatus('Date alignment failed', false);                    return;                }                const commonGold = commonDates.map(date => ({ date, value: goldMap.get(date) }));                const commonOil = commonDates.map(date => ({ date, value: oilMap.get(date) }));                hideError();                setStatus(                    `Updated · ${commonGold.length} trading days (${commonGold[0].date} ~ ${commonGold[commonGold.length - 1].date})`,                    true);                renderChart(commonGold, commonOil, currentMethod);            } catch (e) {                showError(e.message);            }        }        // ---- Alpha Vantage API (with 2s delay between calls) ----        async function fetchAlphaVantageData(apiKey) {            const goldUrl =                `https://www.alphavantage.co/query?function=GOLD_SILVER_HISTORY&symbol=GOLD&interval=daily&apikey=${apiKey}`;            const oilUrl =                `https://www.alphavantage.co/query?function=BRENT&interval=daily&apikey=${apiKey}`;            const goldResp = await fetch(goldUrl);            if (!goldResp.ok) throw new Error('Gold network request failed');            const goldJson = await goldResp.json();            if (goldJson['Error Message'] || goldJson['Note']) {                throw new Error('Gold API error: ' + (goldJson['Error Message'] || goldJson['Note']));            }            const goldSeries = goldJson['data'];            if (!Array.isArray(goldSeries)) throw new Error('Invalid Gold data format');            await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 2000));            const oilResp = await fetch(oilUrl);            if (!oilResp.ok) throw new Error('Oil network request failed');            const oilJson = await oilResp.json();            if (oilJson['Error Message'] || oilJson['Note']) {                throw new Error('Oil API error: ' + (oilJson['Error Message'] || oilJson['Note']));            }            const oilSeries = oilJson['data'];            if (!Array.isArray(oilSeries)) throw new Error('Invalid Oil data format');            const goldArr = goldSeries.map(e => ({ date: e.date, value: parseFloat(e.price) })).filter(e => !isNaN(e            .value));            const oilArr = oilSeries.map(e => ({ date: e.date, value: parseFloat(e.value) })).filter(e => !isNaN(e.value));            return { gold: goldArr, oil: oilArr };        }        // ---- Demo data generator ----        function generateDemoData() {            const goldArr = [],                oilArr = [];            let goldVal = 2650,                oilVal = 72;            const start = new Date(2026, 2, 1);            const end = new Date(2026, 6, 16);            const cur = new Date(start);            while (cur <= end) {                const day = cur.getDay();                if (day !== 0 && day !== 6) {                    goldVal += (Math.random() - 0.48) * 22;                    oilVal += (Math.random() - 0.49) * 1.6;                    goldVal = Math.max(2400, Math.min(2900, goldVal));                    oilVal = Math.max(58, Math.min(85, oilVal));                    const ds = formatDate(cur);                    goldArr.push({ date: ds, value: +goldVal.toFixed(2) });                    oilArr.push({ date: ds, value: +oilVal.toFixed(2) });                }                cur.setDate(cur.getDate() + 1);            }            return { gold: goldArr, oil: oilArr };        }        // ---- Loader functions ----        async function loadAPIData(apiKey) {            hideError();            setStatus('Loading API data...', true);            fetchBtn.disabled = true;            demoBtn.disabled = true;            csvLoadBtn.disabled = true;            try {                const res = await fetchAlphaVantageData(apiKey);                alignAndSetData(res.gold, res.oil, 'API');            } catch (err) {                showError(err.message);                setStatus('API load failed', false);            } finally {                fetchBtn.disabled = false;                demoBtn.disabled = false;                csvLoadBtn.disabled = false;            }        }        function loadDemoData() {            hideError();            fetchBtn.disabled = true;            demoBtn.disabled = true;            csvLoadBtn.disabled = true;            try {                const demo = generateDemoData();                alignAndSetData(demo.gold, demo.oil, 'Demo');            } catch (err) {                showError(err.message);                setStatus('Demo data load failed', false);            } finally {                fetchBtn.disabled = false;                demoBtn.disabled = false;                csvLoadBtn.disabled = false;            }        }        async function loadCSVData() {            hideError();            const goldFile = goldCsvInput.files[0];            const oilFile = oilCsvInput.files[0];            if (!goldFile || !oilFile) {                showError('Please select both Gold and Oil CSV files.');                return;            }            setStatus('Parsing CSV...', true);            fetchBtn.disabled = true;            demoBtn.disabled = true;            csvLoadBtn.disabled = true;            try {                const goldText = await goldFile.text();                const oilText = await oilFile.text();                const goldArr = parseCSV(goldText, 'Gold');                const oilArr = parseCSV(oilText, 'Oil');                alignAndSetData(goldArr, oilArr, 'CSV');            } catch (err) {                showError(err.message);                setStatus('CSV load failed', false);            } finally {                fetchBtn.disabled = false;                demoBtn.disabled = false;                csvLoadBtn.disabled = false;                goldCsvInput.value = '';                oilCsvInput.value = '';            }        }        // ---- Event bindings ----        fetchBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {            const key = apiKeyInput.value.trim();            if (!key) { showError('Please enter an API Key'); return; }            loadAPIData(key);        });        demoBtn.addEventListener('click', loadDemoData);        csvLoadBtn.addEventListener('click', loadCSVData);        startDateInput.addEventListener('change', () => {            if (rawGoldData.length && rawOilData.length) {                reapplyFilterAndRender();            }        });        methodButtons.forEach(btn => {            btn.addEventListener('click', () => {                methodButtons.forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));                btn.classList.add('active');                currentMethod = btn.dataset.method;                if (rawGoldData.length && rawOilData.length) {                    reapplyFilterAndRender();                }            });        });        // ---- Init with demo data ----        window.addEventListener('load', () => {            apiKeyInput.placeholder = 'e.g. YOUR_ALPHA_VANTAGE_KEY';            loadDemoData();        });    })();</script>]]>
    </content>
